    "body": "Consider `nvim_create_autocmd`'s first parameter:\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n    \"name\": \"nvim_create_autocmd\",\r\n    \"since\": 9,\r\n    \"parameters\": [\r\n      [\r\n        \"Object\",\r\n        \"event\"\r\n      ],\r\n      [\r\n        \"Dictionary\",\r\n        \"opts\"\r\n      ]\r\n    ],\r\n    \"return_type\": \"Integer\",\r\n    \"method\": false\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nThe parameter is described as an `Object`. This is because the first argument can be either a `String` or an `ArrayOf(String)`.\r\n\r\nClient API generators could generate nicer APIs if the two possible types were explicitly described, e.g. `String|ArrayOf(String)` or `Union(String,ArrayOf(String))`. I don't care much about syntax (especially since I also opened https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22858 ) :).",
